            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The helix bug was triggered by an upgrade from the unicode version 15 to 16, looking at the updates in the unicode standard, I found that they changed the definition of [Indic Conjunct Break](https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr44/tr44-34.html#Indic_Conjunct_Break) which seems to be related to this bug. I'm not sure how neovim handles unicode, but it would be nice if we could compile the latest commit that used unicode 15 and see if it still triggers the bug, any tips on how to find that commit would be very helpful.",
